Security Concerns:

The code directly interpolates student IDs into HTML using template literals, which could be vulnerable to XSS attacks. Consider using proper HTML escaping.

Photo URLs are directly inserted into img tags without validation, which could be a security risk.

Inconsistencies:

There are two different updateStudentsTable functions with different implementations

Student object properties are inconsistent ( first_name/ last_name vs name)

Some places use student_id while others use id

Code Structure Issues:

The $updateStudentsTable() call in the updateStudent function appears to have a typo ($ prefix)

There's duplicate code for rendering student rows in different functions

Accessibility Issues:

Modal dialog could use better ARIA attributes

Image elements need better alt text descriptions

Form labels could be more descriptive

Here's how you could improve some of these issues:

// Safer student row rendering with XSS protection
function renderStudentRow(student) {
    const escapedName = escapeHtml(student.name);
    const escapedCourseName = escapeHtml(student.course_name);
    const photoUrl = student.photo_url ? escapeHtml(student.photo_url) : '';

    return `
        <tr>
            <td>${student.student_id}</td>
            <td>${escapedName}</td>
            <td>${student.birth_date}</td>
            <td>${student.age}</td>
            <td>${escapedCourseName}</td>
            <td>${photoUrl ?
                `<img src="${photoUrl}"
                     alt="Photo of ${escapedName}"
                     style="width: 50px; height: 50px; object-fit: cover;"
                     onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='default-photo.png';">`
                : 'No photo available'}</td>
            <td>
                <button class="btn btn-warning btn-sm"
                        onclick="updateStudent(${student.student_id})"
                        aria-label="Edit ${escapedName}'s information">
                    <i class="fas fa-edit" aria-hidden="true"></i> Edit
                </button>
                <button class="btn btn-danger btn-sm"
                        onclick="deleteStudent(${student.student_id})"
                        aria-label="Delete ${escapedName}'s record">
                    <i class="fas fa-trash" aria-hidden="true"></i> Delete
                </button>
            </td>
        </tr>
    `;
}

// Helper function to escape HTML
function escapeHtml(unsafe) {
    return unsafe
        .replace(/&/g, "&amp;")
        .replace(/</g, "&lt;")
        .replace(/>/g, "&gt;")
        .replace(/"/g, "&quot;")
        .replace(/'/g, "&#039;");
}

// Unified updateStudentsTable function
function updateStudentsTable(students) {
    const tbody = document.getElementById('studentsList');
    tbody.innerHTML = students.map(student => renderStudentRow(student)).join('');
}

